250 g Ground Beef
6 unit(s) Flour Tortillas
½ cup Tomato Salsa
1 unit(s) Lime
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
113 g Yellow Onion, chopped
56 g Red Cabbage, shredded
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
1 tbsp Tex-Mex Paste
1 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high. When hot, add beef and onions to the dry pan. Cook for 4-5 min, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.**
Carefully drain and discard excess fat.
Add Tex-Mex paste, then stir to combine.
Remove from heat, then transfer beef to a medium bowl. Cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, cut lime into wedges.
Core, then thinly slice pepper into 1/4-inch pieces.

To another medium bowl, squeeze the juice of a lime wedge (two wedges for 4 servings), then add a pinch of sugar and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil.
Add cabbage and peppers, then season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat.

To a small bowl, add sour cream, then squeeze in the juice of a lime wedge (two wedges for 4 servings). Season with salt, pepper and a pinch of sugar, then combine.

Just before serving, wrap tortillas in paper towels.
Microwave for 30 sec-1 min, until tortillas are warm and flexible. (TIP: You can skip this step if you don't want to warm the tortillas.)

Divide tortillas between plates. Spread crema onto tortillas
Top tortillas with beef, veggies, cabbage and feta.
Serve salsa alongside.

If you've opted to get beef, omit oil, then add beef and onions to the dry pan. Cook beef in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the chorizo.** Remove and discard excess fat, if desired.